# Project Structure

Each project lives in its own GitHub repo (`b0ndt/<project-name>`):

```
<project>/
├── docs/
│   ├── requirements/              ← Phase 1
│   ├── architecture/              ← Phase 2
│   │   └── adr/
│   ├── design/                    ← Phase 3 + 4
│   │   ├── design-exploration.md  ← Design directions (Phase 3 — text prompts only)
│   │   ├── approved-direction.md  ← Selected variant (pipeline writes after HitL)
│   │   ├── mockups/               ← AI-generated mockups (PNG — pipeline via NanoBanana)
│   │   ├── design-spec.md         ← Extracted design spec (Phase 4)
│   │   ├── visual-prompts.md      ← Brand asset prompts (Phase 4 — text only)
│   │   └── v0-scaffold.md         ← Optional v0 code scaffold (pipeline)
│   └── reviews/                   ← Phase 6
├── design-system/                 ← Phase 4
│   ├── tailwind.config.ts
│   ├── globals.css
│   └── components/ui/
├── screens/                       ← Phase 4
├── public/                        ← Brand assets (PNG — pipeline via NanoBanana)
├── src/                           ← Phase 5
├── tests/
├── vercel.json
└── README.md
```

## Conventions

- All documentation in Markdown, diagrams in Mermaid
- Date format: YYYY-MM-DD
- File naming: kebab-case
- Cross-reference: REQ → ADR → Design → Code → Review
